Main Branch 1.0.81xxx Release 2026-02-11

Up to date as of 3rd Feb, doesn't include latest test changes

Design

Added new national ambition - Control three of each Legendary Improvement
Changed Control Six Legendary Cities national ambition to Control Five Legendary Cities
Send 20 luxuries is now a tier 9 ambition instead of a national ambition
Disciples can now clear vegetation
Cannot build an improvement that removes vegetation if the unit cannot clear the vegetation
Traders no longer get a court merchant when founding their seat 
Prevented building improvements on Marsh, except for Farms with Centralization
All fresh water sources supply fresh water to their own tile in addition to adjacent tiles
Remove Free Silk and Free Ebony bonus tech cards
Moved Free Porcelain bonus card to be unlockd by Coinage and reduced tech cost accordingly
Free Porcelain and Free Perfume bonus cards now give 2 instances of their luxuries
Autonomous Rule project is removed when a city is breached
Characters cannot give birth more than once a year (relevant for non-yearly turn scales)
Free laws that replace an existing law do not increment the law change count
Raiders can capture empty cities and city sites
Adjustments to Family Archetype character tendencies:
Champions have more Zealots and less Heroes
Riders have more Heroes and less Zealots
When randomly assigning archetypes, characters with governor effect traits are much more likely to be assigned a governor archetype, and similarly general archetypes for characters with general traits
Killing Raiders now contributes towards goals to kill units of their original tribe
Raiders are less stubborn about raiding, if the shortest path is blocked, and will hit opportunity targets instead
Doubled Master/Elder Scribe money per Citizen, to +2/+4
Anchoring and Unlimbering states are not interrupted by attacks that apply new cooldowns (i.e. Immobilize, Stun)
Killed civilian units now count for Assyrian orders, Hero Leader Training, Epics Culture, etc
Units can pass through hostile civilian units, as long as they don't end their movement on their tile
Families and Religions get upset when their civilian units get killed and suffer -20 opinion for 40 turns per unit killed
Improvements to Carthage campaign persistency
Increased maximum effect of god opinion on religion opinion in Wrath of Gods scenario (200 -> 500)
Reduced Tribal raid range in Wrath of Gods scenario
Disabled Venerate mission for and demands being given by Abandoned god in Wrath of Gods scenario 

Programming

Unity updated from 2022.3 to 6.3
Graphics code converted to Unity's Universal Rendering Pipeline
The URP upgrade improves graphics performance, letting the game render with fewer draw calls and use fewer shader variants
Many UI optimizations
Memory leak fixes
Improvements to Safe Mode
AI border expansion tweaks
AI law value correction to avoid frequent changes
Added Latin supplemental characters U+100 to U+17F to Avalon, Trajan and Judson assets, to assist Polish translation mods

UI

Restart Game button renamed Reroll Game. This keeps the same map and preserves nation/dynasty of random AI opponents but now rerolls the random seed
New Map button renamed to Reroll Map. This button is not shown for games on predefined maps
Valid Improvements, Rural, and Urban worker filters show improvements valid anywhere in the city rather than just for current tile
End Turn button now always eligible to be clicked with 0 orders, will cycle to required items when clicked
Added Reset option when editing hotkeys
Character XP is now shown when they have upgraded at least once but progress to next level is 0
Added Peak Legitimacy and Peak Legitimacy per Leader to Hall of Fame (requires regenerating HOF for existing games, won't display on very old saves)
Added on-map icon to units that have been disarmed
Added hotkey for extending turn time (Alt-E)
Updated ZOC help text
Enabled gold cost to buy yields for recommended improvements tooltip
Added color-coding for Send/Return text in Luxury Management
Improved consistency of city build production cost tooltips
Trait opinion of leader now shown in trait tooltip even without advanced help text
Pagan religions are shown in the Adopt State Religion menu even without Divine Rule, with explanatory text
Yields from disciples on improvements are shown when disciples are selected
Anchor mission help text includes water control range
Condensed enlist ability help text
Greyed out effect for dead character portraits applied more consistently
Improved Settler Found City tooltip
Cities with zero yield are included in the nation yield breakdown
When a non-server network game has disconnected human players and the turn timer is counting down, a warning is displayed next to the turn time 
Improvements to Citrus resource and Grove models
Improvements to Ruins model

